How to create custom variables ?

Creating custom variables and tag templates in Google Tag Manager (GTM) lets you extend GTM's built-in functionality. 
Here's a beginner-friendly, step-by-step guide to help you with both:

✅ Part 1: Creating a Custom Variable
Custom variables in GTM are useful for capturing data from your site or scripts that GTM doesn’t automatically track.

🛠️ Example: Create a JavaScript Variable
Steps:
Go to your GTM dashboard.

On the left menu, click Variables.

Click New (under “User-Defined Variables”).

Click on Variable Configuration.

Scroll down and choose Custom JavaScript.

Paste in this example code:

javascript
Copy
Edit
function() {
  return document.title; // This returns the page's title
}
Name your variable, e.g., Page Title Custom JS.

Click Save.

You can now use this variable in tags, triggers, or other variables.